# Cursor Rules for Matías Bilkis Personal Website

## Project Context
This is a Jekyll-based personal academic/professional website for Matías Bilkis, showcasing multiple professional profiles: Academic researcher, Business (QutSur CEO), Developer, Ecosystem Builder, and Speaker/Outreach.

## Code Style & Structure

### File Organization
- **Data files**: All dynamic content in `_data/*.yml` files
- **Pages**: Content pages in `_pages/*.md` using Markdown + Liquid
- **Layouts**: Reusable templates in `_layouts/`
- **Assets**: CSS in `assets/css/`, images in `assets/images/`

### YAML Data Files
- Use consistent structure across similar content types
- Always include `order` field for sorting
- Use descriptive field names
- Group related fields together

### Markdown Pages
- Use front matter for metadata
- Keep content readable and well-structured
- Use Liquid templating for dynamic content
- Include inline styles when needed (but prefer CSS files)

### CSS Guidelines
- Use semantic class names
- Maintain consistent color scheme (#223568 primary, #1976d2 accent)
- Ensure responsive design (mobile-first approach)
- Use card-based layouts for content sections

## Content Management

### Adding New Content
1. **Publications**: Add to `_data/publications.yml` with `order`, `title`, `url`, `description`
2. **Talks**: Add to `_data/talks.yml` with event details and links
3. **Activities**: Add to `_data/activities.yml` with date, location, description
4. **Projects**: Add to `_data/projects.yml` with GitHub link, tech stack, description
5. **QutSur**: Update `_data/qutsur.yml` for business information
6. **Ecosystem**: Update `_data/ecosystem.yml` for ecosystem building activities

### Navigation
- Always update `_data/nav.yml` when adding new major sections
- Keep navigation items in logical order
- Use lowercase, URL-friendly names

## Professional Profiles

The website showcases 5 distinct profiles:
1. **Academic**: Research, publications, QML-CVC group
2. **Business**: QutSur consultancy, services, team
3. **Developer**: GitHub projects, coding portfolio, HPC work
4. **Ecosystem Builder**: Edge City Esmeralda, partnerships
5. **Speaker/Outreach**: Talks, panels, public engagement

## Design Principles

### Visual Hierarchy
- Homepage should immediately show all 5 profiles
- Use clear section headings
- Profile photo should be prominent on homepage
- Cards and sections should be visually distinct

### User Experience
- First impression matters for both clients and employers
- Content should be easy to scan
- Links should be clearly visible
- Mobile responsiveness is critical

### Content Presentation
- Use cards for grouped content
- Include expandable sections for detailed info
- Provide multiple ways to access content (direct links, embedded content)
- Show dates and locations for events

## Technical Guidelines

### Jekyll/Liquid
- Use `site.data.*` to access YAML data
- Sort collections using `sort` filter
- Use `forloop.index` for unique IDs
- Include proper escaping for user-generated content

### Performance
- Optimize images (use appropriate sizes)
- Minimize inline styles (prefer CSS files)
- Use lazy loading for iframes and images
- Keep JavaScript minimal and efficient

### Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML
- Include alt text for images
- Ensure sufficient color contrast
- Make interactive elements keyboard-accessible

## Common Patterns

### Content Cards
```html
<div class="content-card">
  <h3 class="card-title">{{ item.title }}</h3>
  <div class="card-meta">...</div>
  <div class="card-description">{{ item.description }}</div>
  <div class="card-links">...</div>
</div>
```

### Data Structure
```yaml
- title: "Item Title"
  order: 1
  description: "Description"
  url: "https://..."
  year: 2025
  links:
    - name: "Link Name"
      url: "https://..."
```

## When Making Changes

1. **Test locally**: Always run `bundle exec jekyll serve` before committing
2. **Check mobile**: Verify responsive design on mobile devices
3. **Validate YAML**: Ensure YAML syntax is correct
4. **Update navigation**: Add new pages to nav if they're major sections
5. **Maintain consistency**: Follow existing patterns and styles

## File-Specific Rules

### `index.md` (Homepage)
- Should showcase all 5 professional profiles
- Include profile photo
- Provide clear navigation to detailed pages
- Keep it concise but informative

### `_data/*.yml` files
- Use consistent field names
- Always include `order` for sorting
- Use arrays for multiple items
- Include relevant metadata (dates, locations, links)

### `_pages/*.md` files
- Use front matter for layout and permalink
- Include page title
- Use Liquid to iterate over data files
- Add inline styles if page-specific

## Notes

- The `conf/` directory is private (not deployed)
- Profile image: `assets/images/mati_web.png`
- Color scheme should remain professional and consistent
- External links should open in new tabs
- Always provide fallbacks for missing data

